caption: Came here for brunch on Saturday, got the Breakfast Burger, my friend got the Quiche du Jour. Both were amazing! My friend was impressed with the portion size of the quiche and I felt the same way about my burger - Which has two patties AND a fried egg in it, and comes with fries!! It was delicious. Fries could’ve been better but I’m not complaining. Probably had to wait to get a table outside for 15 minutes after coming around 12:30 but not bad at all. Would definitely recommend this place. And their bellini was great too.
Coffee and specialty bar drinks? Count me in.
Chill vibes and great drinks
Highly recommended! Great food  and delicious drinks. Awesome service! This is a Very special place !
The drinks were delicious were delicious and everyone is so lovely!
Love this place! Ordered the black bean burger and smash burger with fries and both were delicious! The restaurant itself has cool vibes. Everyone there is also super nice. Highly recommend! :)
Was just walking down the street when I spotted this cute little bar. The bartender knew his stuff about the craft beers they had in a can and was able to pair me with exactly what I was looking for.

I can say for sure that I like this place. I used to live on 76th street recently and in this place we always meet with my friend, take a coffee with fresh croissant and talk talk. Nice place with cozy atmosphere. Perfect for drink night and brunch.

Don’t know about the food yet as the place is pretty new but the cocktails are amazing! Definitely going again. Plus I like the vibe/ hip kind of but cool. Not so much of that kind in the neighborhood! Coffee is good too
Great atmosphere, food, service and the best well balanced cocktails in Bay Ridge.

OMG!!! Adorable cafe in Bayridge and if you do nothing else in life, please order this decadent OLIVE OIL CAKE for your next gathering. It’s nuts, served with fresh basil, an Aepeol pure and candied tangerines. I don’t even have the words. I also have none left because they ate the damn thing up in 5 minutes!
Be happy that we renegade that place yesterdaywhen I do do painting and I work yeah I love this place and it's very friendly people and horses and everybody and would work as a team player
The food was amazing French toast was very tasty and soft. Everything overall very delish.
Great place to visit very clean and Edwin is a great guy over there
Awesome spot with great coffee, food and mixed drinks.
Great crew!!
they take very long time to prepare the order
Wonderful service and food was good

Looks good I never ate here although Google thinks I did .got stuck on the red light accross from it. It's all pork and bacon and things I don't eat .but I give it to any small business today. Mabey give some halal and strickly vegetarian dishes for this healthy area.
All ways a high quality experience here.
Amazing service, burrito was delicious. Try the butternut squash hot sauce!!
Delicious food and incredible customer service! So happy this place in bay ridge exists!
Lovely decor, staff, food and coffee. Very addictive! When it’s 2pm and you realize you haven’t had breakfast yet, get the Sunrise Sandwich.
Good food, good beer, win win.
Good place to warm up on a cold day
Triple threat. Great drinks (cocktails and beer), food, and coffee. Bartenders are super knowledgeable. Don't miss this place if you are in the area.
Wonderful local cafe. The coffee is always great. They have a regularly rotating beer selection as well. Service is friendly.

This snug coffee bar makes the most of it's space, transforming in the evening into an amazing cocktail bar. The food is the standout though. The quality and uniqueness of the menu items coming out of it's tiny kitchen are leaps and bounds better than most other neighborhood restaurants.

Came here for the brunch. Got a breakfast burrito. It was pretty good. Service was friendly, atmosphere was pleasant. Others got some egg dish and another got a burger. It all looked good and had a taste to match.
Excellent food and cocktails.
Great cocktails, liquor selection and friendly staff.
Surprisingly good bahn mi and coffee

Very good food! Had the kale quinoa salad and it was absolutely delicious and so fresh and warm. Food tastes very fresh and homemade. The iced coffee is wonderful too. A bit small inside but seating is still very easy to find. Waitress was very polite and sweet, will come again!

The neighborhood was long overdue for a spot like this. The perfect mix of laid back and hip while not trying too hard. A chill spot that attracts a chill crowd. Great mixed drinks and bites. We love coming here!

Small, quiet, pleasant. I was not in there for the "cocktail bar" experience. Was in there twice just for one thing the lox on bialy. I know I can go t a bagel store for that, but, ya need to trust me on this, it's not your average bialy and lox. I will not tell you what's on it, or, about the cornucopia of flavors it produces, ya need to go try it out.

Awesome spot! Their burgers are amazing, their drinks are experimental and fun, the fries are great, the servers are lovely, and the atmosphere is really nice.  (The Gremlins movie was on in the background!) Try this place out, you won't be disappointed.  I'm definitely going to return and, next time, I'll be trying their dessert!  Update: Came back a couple of times, as I said I would, and was not disappointed. Their French toast is great, the horchata iced coffee is THE BOMB, and their homemade chips are so delicate they almost melt in your mouth. Never had anything like that before!  New favorite spot, for sure.
Food was good, portion size was pretty big, and ppl were friendly. Came here on a Sunday when it opens at 8am but the kitchen didnt open until 930am and the extra workers didn't come in until 9:45am.
Amazing chocolate croissants.
Incredible brunch; great coffee
Food is delicious. Wish there was decaf coffee, but the service can improve. It really depends on which server you get. Had to ask for the check a couple of times.
Good brunch items. Recommend the Doctor Bird French Toast
Food is excellent, space is nice.  I come  and meet my friends here all the time.
Yummy iced latte. Truffle fries was amazing! Definitely recommend
Our waitress was lovely, and the avocado toast I ordered was delish (I also got to try the Blood Orange cider and it did not disappoint)!
Food was excellent
Amazing food!
One of my fave places to hang and work.
Best coffee cocktails and food in bay ridge! Everything has a perfect balance and you can tell the high quality of the products they use!
Food is good, but this girl with dark hair that works at the bar , her attitude is bad , don’t want to go there anymore not to see her . She looks at you like you own her smth , bad vibes
Best #2 spot in all 3rd avenue. There's a big mirror and everything. The lighting is good if you want to look at the tp after you wipe.
I was incredibly surprised to see anything at all below 5 stars. This place kills it in the food, coffee, and cocktail department. Staff is wonderful and attentive. Wish I went in sooner!
Delicious food and great staff.
Absolutely a gem! Love the variety and atmosphere. Wish I lived nearby!
Maybe the food and the coffee here is good but the Russian chick that works there needs attitude correction.
The food here is amazing! Come for brunch, then stay for dinner! The coffee is top notch and the BLT is amazing! It's hard not to come here every weekend!
Could have bigger portions for the $

Alright, 3-star only coz personnel were super kind and nice and the latte was actually decent (I believe beans were Cafe Grumpy). Why not 5-star? I've called 5 mins prior to arrival to make sure they have avocado toast. They (super politely) come back with a "I'm sorry, we are out of avocados" (no biggie, although upsetting that my earlier call was a waste). Ordered egg Benedict - it looked nice but tasted super blunt and lacked salt (had to ask for salt). That said, my friend got a burrito, it took good 20 minutes AFTER my egg Benedict was served (and yup, they actually suggested a free drink just for the long wait, we've politely said "we appreciate the gesture but no free drink is necessary") and *wait for the punchline* fried potato was salty beyond belief. I personally like salty (hence asking for salt for my egg Benedict) and yet when I tried my friend's fried potatoes it was like weirdly salty. I've politely notified them that the potatoes are super salty and they asked if we'd like a new one that has no salt or has less salt. We've agreed. New batch was as salty as first one (SUPER SALTY). My friend (being super hungry) basically ate the burritos and left potatoes after being "poisoned by the amount of salt in them". Personnel asked if the new batch is good and I asked if they want an honest answer or a kind one - they got my point. Once again - super nice personnel. Kitchen seems to be a disorganized "mess".  P.S. That same kind personnel said they'll give us a break on the bill for all the troubles. Ready? Their applied discount was $1 (ONE DOLLAR). 3-star just went down to 1-star. Are they testing our kindness?  **update:** After I asked "was $1 the discount you've mentioned earlier" she realized how comical that $1 discount was and came back with "I've removed the latte from the bill" line. Going up to 2-star. Not coming back again.  **RESPONSE TO OWNER RESPONSE** We’ve politely rejected the idea of getting a free croissant or a beer now what’s insulting is that the price of the beer is way more than a buck and upon realizing our kindness of not taking free drinks we’ve been given a $1 break on our bill as 10% off one dish. Seriously? After the whole trifecta of failures the least your polite team could do is either wipe up the bill or cut it to 50% but giving literally a buck break is beyond my understanding of well run hospitality business. Thanks for the invite, but thanks no. Well deserved 1-star after such a weak response.
Sunday Brunch was perfect. Guava Bellinis were delicious. I loved the Eggs Benedict with lox and latke, perfect dill hollandaise. Boyfriend had yummy waffle and fried chicken.
Loved the atmosphere. Staff was friendly and helpful, the coffee was great. My favorite cafe in the neighborhood! Reminds me of Seattle coffee houses 💕
Eggs benny' probably the healthiest breakfast I ever had and the staff are outstanding

Wow what a great coffee shop! This place serves some good coffee and excellent food. Avocado toast is a must but the real winner, in my opinion, is the sunrise sandwich. All the food there, is great, the rosemary potatoes are amazing. Any food and coffee you get will be very good. The best part is their service and hospitality, they want to make you feel at home, this is definitely a place to go to if you are in Bay Ridge.
Best brunch options in Bay Ridge! The rest of the hood needs to catch up.
great place for morning coffee and night out drinks! Loved avocado toast and sunrise sandwich❤
One of the better brunch places in Bayridge.

Great STRONG coffee during the day, amazing cocktails at night. My fiance and I frequent MATTER, almost on a weekly basis. The staff is awesome and friendly. It's a great addition to the nightlife of Bay Ridge.
Excellent food, excellent service. Highly recommend their brunch! 👌
Gets really loud after 7pm, I don't think the bar aspect will take off that wel

Best coffee in South Brooklyn, hands down. Best cocktails in South Brooklyn, hands down. Great for a quick bite, a day-long stay to work remotely from, or just a hangout at the bar on a Thursday night. Service staff is great, food is inventive and tasty. This place has become a near daily part of my life.
Perfect for a lunch with my 8 year old.
Had a yummy Bloody Mary and something from the brunch menu. Very pleasant atmosphere and friendly staff. Will have to come back to try the coffee.

Nice little coffee shop. Seating is sparse. Food menu was not displayed when I went there so I had no idea what they offered. If you don't know how to act in a hipster coffee shop then it might be too niche for you

Truly a hidden gem. I started going to Matter when they first opened, mostly for the bread pudding but also because of the great coffee. Now, that they’ve added to their menu, I love coming on the weekends for their brunch items or their delicious burger for lunch.  I’m happy that they’re doing so well in Bay Ridge (even though sometimes it’s hard to find a seat when they get busy on the weekends).  It’s also a great place to come and study  if you come early enough... they’ve got a big, long table.
Amazing cocktails and a delicious menu. I especially like the Banh Matter sandwich.
Really good cocktails but not cheap. Very friendly staff.
Super chill spot with great staff
Great avocado toast and pastries. Have to try their coffee but assuming its going to be good. Great service.

Great coffee shop! BF and I shared a bread pudding. Wait staff offered to warm it up and put fruit compote on top. Yum. Excellent fresh iced teas. Comfortable environment for studying and writing. 2 thumbs up.
Everyone was very nice and the food and drinks were tasty.

The best cafe in Bay Ridge hands down. The coffee is excellent, the food is unique and comforting, while affordable, and whenever you come in you will always be greeted by a friendly worker who clearly cares about the business and your satisfaction. I’m yet to come in and NOT have a great conversation with a happy face behind the counter. Good people, good coffee, good food. Now get off your phone or computer and GO HERE.

Good food, good Brooklyn roasted coffee, good teas, excellent vibe, even good beer and liquors. Finally a 21st century nonpretentious but very well civilized business like this one in Bay Ridge. This is something one would more expect to find in North Brooklyn. We need more like this on 3rd and even 5th.

very cool to have a place serving great coffee, tea, and beer open from morning to night  it's unique for this neighborhood, very glad to have this option in Bay ridge  great to relax, chat, or do work
Great Coffee, cookie, and conversation!
great place for quick bites as well as evening cocktails and morning coffee😋

Coffee and pastries during the day, banging cocktails at night. Some of the best cocktails starting at 5 everyday! The bar program just got started six weeks ago and it rocks. Nothing like it in the area but also worth traveling from afar.

Their excellent coffee uses Cafe Grumpy beans. My favorite pastries include the almond (chocolate or plain) croissant and the bread pudding, which they make in-house. I can vouch for their double cheeseburger and banh mi (the bread is delicious), which you should try if you're really hungry. Otherwise opt for the egg sandwich or avocado toast if you want a lighter meal.
Great little place and their food is REALLY GOOD! Get the avocado toast!

The wife and I really like this place. They have a kitchen in the back so they always have a fresh cake or bread pudding on the counter. The real inspiration for the review is their cheese burger. Top 5 maybe even top 3 best burgers I’ve had in my lifetime.. and it’s from a coffee shop!!
I’ve only been here twice, but both times the baristas went out of their way to take care of me. The espresso is amazing, and the food is delicious.
Avocado toast was great as was the coffee (Grumpy). Super nice staff.
Great coffee. Friendly people.
Love the cozy vibe here... feels like home. Great space for a quick or long cup of tea or coffee, depending on your mood (and timeframe).
Best coffee place in bay ridge, by far! The staff is friendly and welcoming. The chef is accommodating and makes amazing food! Comes with your family and friends!
Great staff and great coffee
Excellent coffee and staff. Big fan!!
Fantastic Cafe, great place to go and have some coffee and work on a laptop all morning!
Great coffee and milk selection, friendly atmosphere and sooo cosy
Great coffee (so happy to have a place serving Grumpys in Bay Ridge!) chill staff and nice atmosphere. Looking forward to them serving beer soon as well.
This is your spot if you're looking for excellent cappuccino. And don't forget to get some cheddar biscuits with that. 👌
Awesome coffee. The staff is really nice. Their pastries are good too!

The cold brew coffee was amazing, even the decaf that we sampled. Doreen the barista was a sweetheart, and knowledgeable. The owner spent time talking to us about the pastries and coffee...very cool guy! Pastries are YUM!! Thank you guys for the experience.
Excellent coffee and great group of people running this great new shop.
Fantastic new coffee shop. Skip the Starbucks, this is real coffee in a cool space.
Amazing coffee, friendly staff and welcoming decor!
Cafe Grumpy Coffee served, nice pastries, ample seating, wifi, friendly...a welcome addition to the 'Ridge'
